cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CL, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a system that uses a deep image captioning network to analyze images captured by planetary rovers. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed system involves the use of natural language processing and machine learning techniques to automate the search for scientific features in images. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on improving the efficiency of planetary exploration missions with rovers. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The system involves natural language processing for specifying search tasks in natural language. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The proposed system can also be deployed as a content-based search engine for ground-based planetary data systems.
